## 9. Summary\
\
**Your instinct is right:** B+C saves the most writing while giving you the most market coverage. Layer persona variants (C) on top of topic specialization (A), and add progressive depth (B) only for Tier 1 topics that justify it.\
\
**The series wrapper solves your metadata question.** Author it once per series, inherit everywhere, override per book only when needed.\
\
**Each book stands alone because:**\
- Different topic = different search term = different market\
- Different persona = different voice = different listener\
- Different engine = different therapeutic story = different value\
- Same mechanism truth = consistent quality = brand trust\
\
**The writing savings are real:**\
- Mechanisms, arcs, contracts, validation = author once\
- Engines = author once per topic\
- Templates = author once per persona\
- Variables = author once per persona\'d7location\
- Atoms = the real writing, but constrained by everything above so each atom is ~60% less effort than free-writing\
\
**The catalog grows multiplicatively** while writing effort grows additively. That's the Phoenix advantage.\
