\fs26 \cf2 \cb9 This analysis is solid. A few honest additions and pushback on specific points:\
\
**What you got exactly right**\
\
The spam signature is not the slot names \'97 it's the rhythm. When every chapter has the same cadence (big opening \uc0\u8594  scene \u8594  story \u8594  teaching \u8594  do this \u8594  wrap), the listener stops hearing the content and starts hearing the pattern. That's the real risk, and your diagnosis is correct.\
\
**Where I'd push back or add**\
\
Option 2 (positional reordering) is the riskiest of the five, and I'd caution against making it a general feature. REFLECTION before SCENE changes the emotional logic of the chapter \'97 you're asking the listener to process a mechanism they haven't yet been given context for. Some reorders are safe (SCENE before HOOK in a story-led chapter), others break comprehension. If you build reorder_mode, you need semantic slot dependency rules, not just "compatible" flags. Otherwise writers will produce chapters that don't track.\
\
Option 3 (chapter archetypes) is the right primary lever \'97 but the archetypes need to be tied to arc position, not just slot weight. A MECHANISM_HEAVY chapter reads differently in chapter 2 vs. chapter 9 even if the slots are identical. The archetype should carry: slot policy, exercise mode, word budget, AND arc role (introduce / deepen / challenge / resolve). That's four variables, not one.\
\
The missing concept in all five options is **chapter weight as a listener experience**. Weight is controlled by the combination of slot presence plus word budget, not slot presence alone. A chapter can have EXERCISE and feel light if the exercise is three lines. A chapter with no EXERCISE can feel heavy if REFLECTION runs 400 words. Your exercise_mode (none/micro/full) gets at this \'97 but it needs a parallel reflection_weight and story_weight concept so the FormatSelector can balance total felt load per chapter, not just count slots.\
\
**Most practical single change**\
\
Make EXERCISE opt-in per chapter with a default of 
\f2 none
\f0 , and gate 
\f2 full
\f0  mode behind a quota check at book level. That alone eliminates the "every chapter feels like a workbook" problem. Everything else is incremental from there.\
\
**What to build next, ordered**\
\
First: chapter archetype \uc0\u8594  slot policy mapping with arc_role field. Second: exercise_mode as an explicit field with quota validator. Third: reflection_weight and story_depth as budget controls per chapter. Fourth: novelty scoring on chapter signature sequences so the planner penalizes three consecutive same-archetype chapters. Reordering last, with hard semantic constraints.\
\
The architecture is not the problem. You don't need to throw away HOOK, SCENE, STORY, REFLECTION, EXERCISE, INTEGRATION. You need the planner to stop applying it uniformly.\
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0

