\fs26 \cf2 \cb9 what do u thunk? Spam avoidance vs. book assembly\
1. Near-duplicate / repetitive content\
spam_avoidance.rtf: No \'93same content with tiny edits, keyword-stuffed variants, machine-spun clones\'94; no \'93catalogs that clutter the store with near-duplicates.\'94\
What you have:\
Structural near-duplicates (covered):\
DupEval / CTSS (scripts/ci/check_platform_similarity.py): structural fingerprint (arc, band_seq, slot_sig, exercise placement, story_fam_vec, ex_fam_vec, tps, role_seq). Block \uc0\u8805  0.78, review \u8805  0.65. Same teacher + same arc + same band sequence \u8594  always block (catalog farm risk).\
Wave density (scripts/ci/check_wave_density.py): FAIL if >30% same arc_id, >40% identical band_seq, >50% identical slot_sig, >60% identical exercise placement, \uc0\u8805 40% identical emotional_role_sig.\
Similarity index (artifacts/catalog_similarity/index.jsonl): append per plan via update_similarity_index.py; CTSS compares new plans to existing catalog.\
Prose-level near-duplicates (gap):\
DupEval is structural only (no prose, embeddings, or NLP). A \'93book-level duplication\'94 design in talp/ (paragraph hash, sentence hash, 6-gram, opening/closing collision) is not in the active CI path. So two books can still share very similar text and pass, as long as structure (arc, bands, slots, etc.) differs.\
Verdict: You\'92re in good shape on structural spam (no template clones, no same-arc-same-band waves). You are not yet enforcing prose-level anti-spam (paragraph/6-gram/opening-closing uniqueness) in the assembly/CI flow.\
2. Structural variety\
spam_avoidance.rtf: \'93Vary chapter counts, section types \'85 instead of just rewording the same outline.\'94\
What you have:\
Format registry with multiple formats (chapter ranges, slot defs); format selection by topic/persona/installment.\
Structural entropy (check_structural_entropy.py): FAIL if one story structure_family > 70%, one exercise family > 60%, one compression family > 70%; min STORY 120w, EXERCISE 90w; emotional_role_sequence and intro/outro style diversity.\
Wave density: prevents waves that are too similar in arc, band_seq, slot_sig, exercise placement, emotional_role_sig.\
Variation selector (e.g. book_structure_id, journey_shape_id, motif/reframe, section reorder) for anti-cluster storytelling.\
Angle_id in CTSS and wave density (e.g. \uc0\u8805 50% same angle_id \u8594  FAIL).\
Verdict: Assembly and CI are aligned with \'93structural variety\'94 and \'93no same outline everywhere.\'94\
3. Release velocity and \'93spray and pray\'94\
spam_avoidance.rtf: \'93Stagger releases and mix series\'94; \'93avoid \'91spray and pray\'92 bursts\'94; \'93Uploading hundreds of extremely similar books in a single day \'85 easy anomaly.\'94\
What you have:\
Teacher Portfolio / Brand matrix (config/catalog_planning/brand_teacher_matrix.yaml): max_books_per_wave, release_spacing_days, max_books_per_brand_per_month; per-teacher max_books_per_topic, max_books_per_persona (e.g. 4 and 5).\
Teacher portfolio planner allocates (teacher, topic, persona, brand) before BookSpec; wave orchestrator selects a balanced wave from candidates (arc/band/slot/ex diversity).\
Verdict: Release pacing and wave mix are controlled so you\'92re not dumping a single structure at once.\
4. Metadata / branding\
spam_avoidance.rtf: \'93Distinct titles and subtitles\'94; \'932\'965 stable imprints/pen names\'94; \'93consistent, non-confusing pen names\'94; no misleading metadata.\
What you have:\
TEACHER_PORTFOLIO_PLANNING_SPEC: metadata entropy (title syntax, subtitle, hook, description); metadata_style_family per teacher to avoid catalog-wide duplication.\
Brand archetype registry, author/narrator registries, brand_author_assignments \uc0\u8594  stable imprints/pen names, not hundreds of throwaway identities.\
Author positioning (e.g. check_author_positioning.py): forbidden language per profile; no \'93official\'94/misleading claims in the way positioning is defined.\
Verdict: Design supports \'93stable imprints\'94 and \'93distinct metadata\'94; enforcement is in config + author checks, not inside the assembly compiler itself.\
5. Low-quality / \'93obviously auto-generated\'94\
spam_avoidance.rtf: \'93Books that are hard to understand, sloppily formatted, or obviously auto-generated \'91junk\'92\'94; \'9390%+ overlapping text, thin intros, generic filler.\'94\
What you have:\
Min word counts (STORY 120w, EXERCISE 90w); story/exercise/compression family caps; no [EXPANDED] in body; emotional curve and role sequence rules.\
Creative Quality Gate v1 (optional): arc motion, transformation density, specificity, ending strength, lexical rhythm.\
Reassurance/phrase caps and TTS rhythm rules in governance.\
Verdict: Assembly + structural entropy + optional quality gate reduce \'93thin, generic, obviously auto-generated\'94 output; prose overlap is still only loosely constrained (no corpus-wide paragraph/6-gram gate).\
Pipeline order and when gates run\
Doc\'92d order: compile \uc0\u8594  structural_entropy_check \u8594  check_platform_similarity \u8594  update_similarity_index \u8594  publish.\
run_pipeline.py and generate_full_catalog.py do compile (and optional render). They do not automatically run the CI scripts above.\
So you stay \'93free of spam stuff\'94 only if you run before publish:\
check_structural_entropy.py\
check_platform_similarity.py (and keep index updated)\
update_similarity_index.py\
check_wave_density.py on the release wave\
If those aren\'92t in your release checklist or automation, a book/wave can ship without the anti-spam gates.\
Short answer\
Yes, for structural and release behavior: Book assembly is designed to stay clear of the main spam patterns in spam_avoidance.rtf: no structural near-duplicates (CTSS + wave density), structural variety (entropy + variation + angles), staggered/controlled releases (brand/teacher matrix + wave selection), stable imprints and metadata diversity, and basic low-quality guards.\
But:\
1) Prose-level near-duplicate checks (paragraph/sentence/6-gram, opening/closing collision) are not in the current assembly/CI path.\
2) Anti-spam only applies if you actually run the CI pipeline (structural entropy \uc0\u8594  platform similarity \u8594  update index \u8594  wave density) before publish.\
If you want to close the prose gap, the next step would be to add a pre-publish step that runs paragraph/6-gram/opening-closing checks (e.g. from the talp duplication-simulator concept) and optionally wire it into the same pipeline order.\
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0

