1. Did the previous implementation do everything needed?\
\
Short answer: No. The gate script and checklist were implemented; wiring to catalog planning/release was not.\
\
What was implemented\
\
\
\
\
\
scripts/ci/run_prepublish_gates.py \'97 Single entrypoint that runs, in fixed order: (1) structural entropy per plan, (2) platform similarity per plan, (3) wave density, (4) prose duplication (wave vs catalog), (5) similarity index update only after 1\'964 pass. Fails hard (exit 1) on any gate failure.\
\
\
\
scripts/ci/check_prose_duplication.py \'97 Corpus-level prose checks: paragraph hash collisions, opening-12-word collision, closing-sentence collision, 6-gram Jaccard overlap (configurable fail/warn thresholds).\
\
\
\
scripts/ci/PREPUBLISH_CHECKLIST.md \'97 Documents the single command, gate order, blocking rules, required inputs, and release decision.\
\
What was not implemented\
\
\
\
\
\
No code path calls run_prepublish_gates. Grep shows:\
\
\
\
\
\
scripts/generate_full_catalog.py stops at wave selection (writes artifacts/waves/wave_selected.txt); it does not run prepublish or render.\
\
\
\
scripts/distribution/pre_export_check.py runs only Gate #49 (locale/territory); it does not invoke run_prepublish_gates.\
\
\
