\fs26 \cf2 \cb9 good? : Wire Pre-Publish Gates to Release and Clarify Compliance Scope\
\
1. Did the previous implementation do everything needed?\
\
Short answer: No. The gate script and checklist were implemented; wiring to catalog planning/release was not.\
\
What was implemented\
\
\
\
\
\
scripts/ci/run_prepublish_gates.py \'97 Single entrypoint that runs, in fixed order: (1) structural entropy per plan, (2) platform similarity per plan, (3) wave density, (4) prose duplication (wave vs catalog), (5) similarity index update only after 1\'964 pass. Fails hard (exit 1) on any gate failure.\
\
\
\
scripts/ci/check_prose_duplication.py \'97 Corpus-level prose checks: paragraph hash collisions, opening-12-word collision, closing-sentence collision, 6-gram Jaccard overlap (configurable fail/warn thresholds).\
\
\
\
scripts/ci/PREPUBLISH_CHECKLIST.md \'97 Documents the single command, gate order, blocking rules, required inputs, and release decision.\
\
What was not implemented\
\
\
\
\
\
No code path calls run_prepublish_gates. Grep shows:\
\
\
\
\
\
scripts/generate_full_catalog.py stops at wave selection (writes artifacts/waves/wave_selected.txt); it does not run prepublish or render.\
\
\
\
scripts/distribution/pre_export_check.py runs only Gate #49 (locale/territory); it does not invoke run_prepublish_gates.\
\
\
\
There is no single \'93release\'94 or \'93export wave\'94 script that runs prepublish before allowing publish.\
\
\
\
So anti-spam is still process-dependent: it only applies if someone manually runs run_prepublish_gates.py before publish. Release automation can currently proceed without running it.\
\
\
\
2. Wiring pre-publish to catalog planning and release\
\
Goal: One mandatory pre-publish command that runs all anti-spam gates in order and fails hard; release automation calls only that command (no manual partial runs).\
\
Recommended approach\
\
Introduce a single release entrypoint that must pass before any export to storefronts. Two concrete options:\
\
Option A \'97 New script: scripts/release/prepare_wave_for_export.py (recommended)\
\
\
\
\
\
Inputs: Wave ID (or explicit --plan-list + --wave-rendered-dir), paths to index and catalog-rendered dir, optional report path.\
\
\
\
Behavior:\
\
\
\
\
\
Resolve plan list (e.g. from artifacts/waves/<wave_id>/plans/*.json or from wave_selected.txt plus a convention for where those plans live).\
\
\
\
Call run_prepublish_gates.py with those plans, wave-rendered dir, catalog-rendered dir, index; capture exit code and report.\
\
\
\
If prepublish passes, optionally run Gate #49 for each plan (or document that Gate #49 is run separately per plan at upload time).\
\
\
\
Exit 0 only if all steps pass; otherwise exit 1.\
\
\
\
Convention: Distribution/upload automation (CI or human-triggered) runs only this script before exporting; if it exits non-zero, export is not attempted. No separate manual runs of individual gates.\
\
Option B \'97 Extend generate_full_catalog.py with --require-prepublish\
\
\
\
\
\
After Step 4 (wave selection), if --require-prepublish is set: run render for the selected wave (or require --wave-rendered-dir), then run run_prepublish_gates on that wave; if it fails, exit 1 and do not write the wave as \'93approved for export.\'94\
\
\
\
Downside: generate_full_catalog does not currently render; adding render + prepublish would mix \'93compile + select wave\'94 with \'93render + validate for release,\'94 and would require the catalog pipeline to produce rendered text for the whole wave, which may be heavy. Option A keeps \'93build wave\'94 and \'93prepare wave for export\'94 as separate steps and only wires the latter to prepublish.\
\
Recommendation: Option A. Implement scripts/release/prepare_wave_for_export.py that:\
\
\
\
\
\
Takes --wave-id (or --plans-dir + --wave-rendered-dir), --index, --catalog-rendered-dir, --report.\
\
\
\
Ensures artifacts/waves/<wave_id>/plans and artifacts/waves/<wave_id>/rendered exist (or equivalent from plan list).\
\
\
\
Invokes run_prepublish_gates.py with the correct arguments; if return code is non-zero, exits 1 and writes report.\
\
\
\
Documents in scripts/ci/PREPUBLISH_CHECKLIST.md and docs/SYSTEMS_V4.md that release automation must call this script (or directly run_prepublish_gates.py) and must not export on non-zero exit.\
\
Catalog planning itself (e.g. generate_full_catalog.py, catalog_planner, wave orchestrator) does not need to call the gate runner; the constraint is that the only path to \'93approved for export\'94 is through the single prepublish command. So either:\
\
\
\
\
\
The release job runs prepare_wave_for_export.py (or run_prepublish_gates.py) and only then runs upload/export, or\
\
\
\
A future \'93export wave\'94 or \'93publish wave\'94 script runs prepare_wave_for_export.py internally and proceeds to export only on success.\
\
That satisfies \'93make release automation call only that command.\'94\
\
\
\
